By Manorama
English | September 2016 | PDF | 98 pages | 11.9 mb
scanned to PDF by me.

History changed when Charles Darwin and his HMS Beagle landed on the Galapagos Islands. Darwin detected many unusual features in the flora and fauna of Galapagos. His observations on the island altered the scientific view on the origins of life. They made Galapagos a 'treasure island'. Not only Galapagos Island but islands in general, have always inspired Man's curiosity, because of their origin and unique biodiversity.
Islands never fail to amuse and interest Man. Apart from their scientific significance, many islands are strong nations too.
This issue of Tell Me Why will help you explore some curious facts about these unique land masses.
